section.p:
To ask the Secretary of State for War to give—


The establishment and strength of officers by ranks of the seventy-four Third Battalions Special Reserve Infantry on the 1st February, 1912, exclusive of Regular Establishment.

The number of officers now serving in the seventy-four Third Battalions Special Reserve who transferred from the Militia.

The total strength of the non-commissioned officers and men of the seventy-four Third Battalions Special Reserve exclusive of Regular Establishment on the 1st February, 1912.


(a) The difference between strength and establishment;

(b) The number of non-commissioned officers and men under 20 years of age;

(c) The number of non-commissioned officers and men whose term of service expires before the 1st February, 1913;


and to ask for the same information in respect to the twenty-seven Extra Special Reserve Battalions.

1. That the provisions of—


The County of Lanark Tramways Order;

The Glasgow Boundaries Order;

The Glasgow Water (Charges) Order;

The Lord Ericht Water and Electric Power Order;

The Lothian Railways Order; and Part III (Water) of the Glasgow Corporation Order
are of such a character that they ought to be dealt with by Private Bill and not by Provisional Order;

Report from the Committee of Selection, that the Lords following be proposed to the House as the panel of Lords to act as Commissioners under the Act, viz.:—


E. Cathcart;

L. Saye and Sele;

agreed to; and the said Lords appointed accordingly.

Report from the Committee of Selection, that the Lords following be proposed to the House as the panel of Lords to act as Commissioners under the Act, viz.:—


E. Mansfield;

L. Bowes (E. Strathmore and Kinghorn);

agreed to; and the said Lords appointed accordingly.
